    "narrative": "Our offensive strategy for April 9 is anchored by the dual-threat upside of **Jose Caballero** (77.16) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.97). **Jose Caballero** remains a must-start; while hitting 8th hurts his counting stat floor, the matchup against the left-handed Springs offers a 13% platoon boost and his 86% SB efficiency against slow deliveries is exactly the aggressive profile Ghost Ride the WHIP requires to secure the scarcest category in this 5x5 format. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** projects as an elite play batting 3rd against the soft-tossing Randy V\u00e1squez (5.43 xERA), where a massive 14% platoon edge and favorable spot in the lineup capitalize on a high-ceiling scoring environment. **Giancarlo Stanton** (67.71) also earns a strong recommendation, as the combination of park factors and the favorable matchup against Springs positions him to drive home runs and RBI.\n\nThe decision to start **Max Muncy** (61.96) over our marginal options highlights the importance of volume and efficiency; he benefits from a 7% platoon advantage against the lefty Weathers and provides a tactical SB boost due to his opportunistic baserunning against slower deliveries. The most difficult decision of the day centered on **Zach McKinstry** (49.64) and **Gabriel Moreno** (43.47). While both are technically active, they sit in the \"marginal\" tier, primarily because **Gabriel Moreno** faces the stiff challenge of Nolan McLean, an elite arm (3.04 xERA). **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.61) narrowly made the cut over our bench depth, buoyed by wind conditions that offset his 15% negative platoon drag against Anthony Kay. We are monitoring the pending lineup statuses for **Gabriel Moreno**, **Kyle Karros**, **Corbin Carroll**, **Mickey Moniak**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino** closely; any downward shift in their projected batting order could jeopardize their efficiency scores, forcing us to lean on our reserves like **Brice Turang**, **Seiya Suzuki**, or **Austin Riley** if they were available, though today\u2019s roster construction relies heavily on the aforementioned starters.",
